# GIT VS GITHUB


### GIT
-It is a distributed version control system (DVCS)

-Manages source code history

-Access: your local system installation

-Scope: local repository management

-Collaboration:
local changes, requires manual sharing

-Usage:
primarily using the command line interface


### GITHUB
-It is a Version Control as a Service (VCaaS)
-It can also be called a "GIT provider"

-Provides cloud storage for GIT repos

-Access through a web interface, because it is a cloud service

-Scope: online collaboration of remote hosting

-Collaboration:
it has integrated tools for collaboration like issues and PRs, and some other
features

-Usage:
it has a graphical interface, and it also has its own CLI-tool, but most
people are interacting with it via website
